        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Hello necros!</P><P>My first post on these forums as Neph.  I have been reading them for some time, and have gotten a lot of good (and bad) insight on the necro class.  But I have a question....</P><P>I played an Erudite necro to 35, and because of these forums I changed to an Iksar.  Neph is now level 20.  I have gotten him the shadowbound armor, Havester, and some of the drops from Dalnir, along with some various caster type pieces.</P><P>So!  On to my question.  </P><P>What do you all feel to be the ONE piece of equipment that a necro should have?</P><P>I am working with dual-boxed 54 mage and 49 cleric.  Mage is primary, and the cleric follows around and is mostly run by hotkeys.  I have never been able to accumulate a large amout of cash (6k is the most I think I have ever had at one time) due to my general unwillingness to sit around and try to sell stuff.  </P><P>So I am curious if there is considerd to be a piece of equipment that will profoundly change the life of a necro that might be relatively easy to aquire cost-wise.  JBoots?  Pre-nerf CoS? (might be too expensive for me)  Staff of Dreaded Gaze?  I am not above long camps, since my main is a mage.  <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle>  But I do tend to do things alone, so the camp can't be too hard.</P><P>What do you all think?  What should I try to get?</P><P> </font></td>

